  "texts": [
    "We included studies published in English that underwent peer review, whether in journals or in the proceedings of conferences, workshops, or symposiums.",
    "Seven types of mechanistic models, commonly used in epidemiological modeling, were considered eligible for this review: compartmental models, individual/ agent-based models, metapopulation models, cellular automata, renewal equations, chain binomial models, and branching processes.",
    "Eligible AI techniques include all ML and DL models, excluding statistical models and fuzzy logic systems.",
    "We define \"integrated models\" as those combining mechanistic epidemiological models with AI techniques specifically for transmission analysis and disease intervention optimization.",
    "Studies that constructed AI techniques as alternative modeling methods, compared the performance of AI techniques with mechanistic models, or used mechanistic models solely to generate validation/testing datasets for AI techniques were not considered eligible under this definition."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}